hedge funds betting on credit bfam’s multistrategy asian opportunities master fund which is expected to end the year with more than  billion of assets gained  percent this year through november said a person with knowledge of the matter who asked not to be named as the information is private about  percent of its returns this year came from credit trades that include buying distressed commodity bonds in the first quarter whose values have since rebounded said chief investment officer benjamin fuchs who declined to comment on returns other trades include the debt restructuring of chinese property developer kaisa group holdings ltd and selling credit default swaps on embattled commodities firm noble group ltd to bearish investors in the first half about half of its return this year came from volatility trades as event such as the uk’s vote to leave the european union and the us elections added to market swingsserica’s credit fund run by ivan lee in hong kong surged more than  percent this year through november said a person with knowledge of the matter the majority of the profit came from the rebound in the value of indonesian and resources company bonds it bought at the beginning of the year said the person it also made money from a number of distressed credit tradesthe  million lim asia special situations fund managed by don ewer and peter warbanoff made  percent after fees in the same period said george long lim’s chief investment officer highyield bonds especially those in the commodity industry recovered as the industry rebounded and as some companies refinanced their debt it also made money from loans including distressed ones it picked up as early as last year that have rebounded in value said long whose hong kongbased multistrategy hedgefund firm has  billion of assets under management another creditrelated hedge fund that shone was ocp asia’s about  billion orchard landmark fund it returned nearly  percent this year through november making direct loans to small and mediumsized companies across the asiapacific region said a person with knowledge of the matter ocp asia manages about  billion out of its singapore and hong kong offices some of this year’s bestperforming large hedge funds didn’t focus on credit dymon asia capital singapore’s  billion macro fund gained about  percent in the  months according to an estimate sent to investors its  million dymon asia currency value fund which focuses on currencies and gold and takes more concentrated bets was up  percent bets on asian currencies particularly the japanese yen to weaken against the dollar drove returns for both separately the  million credence global fund a relativevalue hedge fund that seeks to profit from changes in price relationships between assets made  percent this year according to an investor newsletter on the equity side japan’s benchmark nikkei  stock average edged down  percent through november amid disillusionment with government policies to stoke growth china funds struggled to claw back from losses after the shanghai composite index plunged  percent in january amid concerns about the country’s economic slowdown a falling currency and regulations among some of the funds with losses greenwoods asset management’s  billion golden china fund is down  percent this year according to data compiled by bloomberg symphony financial partners’s sfp value realization fund which invests in japanese companies and works with management to prompt actions such as share buybacks is set to have its first loss since  the fund fell  percent this year through november according to cofounder david baran who said a lot of the volatility and uncertainty that sparked market declines are “somewhat behind us”the  million tantallon fund which trades asiapacific stocks lost nearly  percent this year according to data compiled by bloomberg the fund fell nearly  percent in march in the worst month in its year history when its bearish bets on most regional indexes and bullish bets on dollar suffered according to a newsletter posted on its website rega capital dynamic value fund a longshort china hedge fund fell  percent this year through nov  according to the firm some equityfocused funds bucked the trend ally bridge lb healthcare fund managed by hong kongbased former merck  co scientist li bin made nearly  percent in the first  months according to an update sent to investors the asiafocused fund invests in mostly publicly traded stocks in the industry targeting particularly opportunities created by chinese medical reforms li researched pharmaceutical companies for merrill lynch  co and morgan stanley in new york and hong kong before joining ally bridge groupthe  million rwc asia opportunity fund rose  percent this year according to an emailed statement from londonbased rwc partners winning trades include korean steelmaker posco and japan’s sumco corp said garret mallal the fund’s singaporebased managerunited gain investment’s asean plus three segregated portfolio with  million of assets rose  percent this year said lau chi yiu chief investment officer of the hong kongbased firm that oversees  million of assets profitable trades for the fund that focuses on southeast asia as well as hong kong japan and south korea included indonesian stocks such as noodlesmaker pt tiga pilar sejahtera food tbk and cement maker pt semen baturaja persero tbk representatives from ally bridge greenwoods tantallon and serica declined to comment bloomberg stay updated with markets news on bloombergquint recommended for you blackrock says absolutely critical to look at china bonds shree renuka sugars’ debt will fall to rs  crore post restructuring says murkumbi  bloombergquint poll nifty hits mark what’s next  india’s largest cigarette maker in for a ‘tough’ year say brokerages   dymon asia macro plus fund graypools sign in learn more dymon asia macro plus fund hedge fund institutional investors hedge funds dymon asia macro plus fund dymon asia macro plus fund is a cay